T><FONT FACE="Symbol" SIZE=2> q</FONT><FONT FACE="Times">' = AE / CE</P><P>Let: d = AC and n</FONT><FONT FACE="Symbol" SIZE=2>l</FONT><FONT FACE="Times">= DC + CE</P><P>then: 2AC sin</FONT><FONT FACE="Symbol" SIZE=2> q</FONT><FONT FACE="Times"> = DC + CE </P><P>By substitution, we get Bragg&#146;s law.</P><P ALIGN="CENTER"></P><P ALIGN="CENTER">&nbsp;</P><P ALIGN="CENTER">n</FONT><FONT FACE="Symbol" SIZE=2>l</FONT><FONT FACE="Times"> = 2dsin</FONT><FONT FACE="Symbol" SIZE=2> q</P></FONT><FONT FACE="Times"></FONT></BODY></HTML>